## `<file-level: imports and fixtures>`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-xattrs-1 -->

### Purpose
Tests for extended attributes on files and directories. Uses the `as_root` fixture (most xattr operations require root for `trusted.*`/`security.*` namespaces; `user.*` is unrestricted but tests run as root for simplicity).

### Implementation Notes

```python
import os  # for XATTR_CREATE, XATTR_REPLACE constants
import pytest

from sqlite_fs.errors import (
    AlreadyExists,
    InvalidXattr,
    NotFound,
    PermissionDenied,
)


@pytest.fixture
def fs_with_file(as_root):
    """as_root + a file at /f."""
    fd = as_root.create("/f")
    as_root.close_fd(fd)
    yield as_root
```

Constants:

```python
XATTR_CREATE = os.XATTR_CREATE     # 1 — fail if attr already exists
XATTR_REPLACE = os.XATTR_REPLACE   # 2 — fail if attr does not exist
```

---

## `test_set_and_get_roundtrip(fs_with_file)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-xattrs-2 -->

### Postconditions

```python
fs_with_file.setxattr("/f", "user.tag", b"project-alpha")
assert fs_with_file.getxattr("/f", "user.tag") == b"project-alpha"
```

