## `test_setxattr_create_flag_on_existing_raises(fs_with_file)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-xattrs-6 -->

### Purpose
`XATTR_CREATE` demands the attr does not already exist. Repeated create raises.

### Postconditions

```python
fs_with_file.setxattr("/f", "user.x", b"first")
with pytest.raises(AlreadyExists):
    fs_with_file.setxattr("/f", "user.x", b"second", flags=XATTR_CREATE)
# Original value is unchanged.
assert fs_with_file.getxattr("/f", "user.x") == b"first"
```

---

## `test_setxattr_replace_flag_on_missing_raises(fs_with_file)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-xattrs-7 -->

### Postconditions

```python
