## `test_xattrs_isolated_per_inode(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-xattrs-11 -->

### Purpose
Xattrs on two distinct files are independent. Setting on A does not affect B.

### Postconditions

```python
fd_a = as_root.create("/a"); as_root.close_fd(fd_a)
fd_b = as_root.create("/b"); as_root.close_fd(fd_b)

as_root.setxattr("/a", "user.tag", b"aaa")
assert as_root.listxattr("/b") == []
with pytest.raises(NotFound):
    as_root.getxattr("/b", "user.tag")
```

---

## `test_value_too_large_raises(fs_with_file)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-xattrs-12 -->

### Purpose
Linux limits xattr values to 64 KiB. Our library enforces the same. 65537 bytes is one past the limit.

### Postconditions

```python
ok = b"a" * 65536
fs_with_file.setxattr("/f", "user.big", ok)
assert fs_with_file.getxattr("/f", "user.big") == ok

too_big = b"a" * 65537
with pytest.raises(InvalidXattr):
    fs_with_file.setxattr("/f", "user.bigger", too_big)
```

---

## `test_name_too_long_raises(fs_with_file)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-xattrs-13 -->

### Purpose
Xattr names have a 255-byte upper bound (Linux convention).

### Postconditions

```python
ok = "user." + ("a" * 250)   # 255 bytes total
fs_with_file.setxattr("/f", ok, b"v")

too_long = "user." + ("a" * 251)
with pytest.raises(InvalidXattr):
    fs_with_file.setxattr("/f", too_long, b"v")
```

---

## `test_namespace_trusted_requires_root(fresh_fs)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-xattrs-14 -->

### Purpose
`trusted.*` attributes require root (Linux convention). A non-root user is denied.

### Postconditions

```python
# As root, create the file.
with fresh_fs.as_user(0, 0):
    fd = fresh_fs.create("/f")
    fresh_fs.close_fd(fd)

# As non-root, trusted.* is denied.
with fresh_fs.as_user(1000, 1000):
    with pytest.raises(PermissionDenied):
        fresh_fs.setxattr("/f", "trusted.something", b"v")

# As root, trusted.* works.
with fresh_fs.as_user(0, 0):
    fresh_fs.setxattr("/f", "trusted.something", b"v")
    assert fresh_fs.getxattr("/f", "trusted.something") == b"v"
```

---

## `test_namespace_user_unrestricted(fresh_fs)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-xattrs-15 -->

### Postconditions

```python
with fresh_fs.as_user(0, 0):
    fd = fresh_fs.create("/f", mode=0o666)
    fresh_fs.close_fd(fd)

with fresh_fs.as_user(1000, 1000):
    # user.* is unrestricted (subject to mode bits on the file itself;
    # 0o666 means any user can write).
    fresh_fs.setxattr("/f", "user.tag", b"v")
    assert fresh_fs.getxattr("/f", "user.tag") == b"v"
```

